<title>USA: Safeway Vons agree to merge.</title>
<headline>Safeway Vons agree to merge.</headline>
<dateline>PLEASANTON, Calif. 1996-12-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Safeway Inc and The Vons Cos Inc on Monday said they have agreed to a merger that will create the second largest grocery store chain in North Amerian with 1,377 stores and $22 billion in annual sales.</p>
<p>Safeway, which already owns about 35 percent of Vons stock, said it will issue 1.425 shares of its common for each outstanding share of Vons stock to acquire Vons.</p>
<p>In addition, Safeway has agreed to buy back about 15 million shares of its stock from certain partnerships controlled by affiliates of Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co.  </p>
<p>--</p>
